pseudo class - are used to select and style elements based on the position within the doc tree, without the need for adding extra classes or javascript

selector:pseudo-class{
    property:value;
}

pseudo element - a pseudo element is used to style a specific part of an element.

selector::pseudo-element{
    property:value;
}

buttons
.btn{
    border: none;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 15px;
}

.btn:hover{
    background-color: #923838;
    cursor: pointer;
}

